news.title: Rajasthan housing board increases reserve price of plots after three years
news.para: With this, consumers will have to shell out more money to purchase houses and flats in the RHB colonies and getting its registry.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates among 17 accounts in NARCL's buy list
news.para: Jaiprakash Associates is the second largest account listed, with outstanding loans of Rs 20,167 crore. Its affiliate, Jaypee Cement, with Rs 527 crore loan, is also listed.

news.title: Yours invests Rs 100 crore in co-ownership of luxury property
news.para: Yours has so far acquired assets worth Rs 25 crore in Goa, Alibaug and the Nilgiris and plans to expand to more cities. Every luxury home is being acquired under a special purpose vehicle (SPV), which will have eight shareholders who get to stay in the home for 45 days every year.

news.title: Logix Blossom Greens' builder hikes power tariff four times, withdraws after protest
news.para: ​However, the issue is not over yet, with residents fearing that rates would likely undergo revision in the coming days. They plan to meet the Noida Authority officials on the issue.

news.title: Delhi government to restart construction of 16,000 flats for poor, repair others
news.para: The government has also decided to repair 17,660 flats that have been lying unoccupied for several years and are currently in a dilapidated state.

news.title: Will anyone pay Rs 1,500 crore for hotel site at Chandigarh Sector 17?
news.para: Sources said the collector rate of a Sector-17 shop-cum-office (SCO) is Rs 5,25,405 per square yard, implying the Sector 17 hotel site reserve price is more than Rs 1,500 crore. Sector 17 already has three major big hotels.

news.title: Bengaluru development body site allottees face fine for not building houses within five years
news.para: While BDA is talking tough, site owners are blaming it for not providing basic civic infrastructure to ensure construction activity in the layout. The allottees have written to BDA to extend the deadline by another five years.

news.title: Jaipur municipal corporation-heritage gives 257 land deeds in two days
news.para: Mayor Munesh Gujar distributed 80 land deeds to residents in the Civil Lines zone and Kishanpole zone on Saturday. She asked officers to distribute as many pattas as possible.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA to take Rs 60,000 crore loan for infrastructure projects
news.para: CM Eknath Shinde made the announcement at a post-cabinet briefing on Saturday. Metropolitan commissioner SVR Srinivas said: "We will need this money to execute existing and future projects in MMR."

news.title: Post-survey, Rajasthan government to regularise colonies having 20-feet roads
news.para: To boost Prashashan Shahron ke Sang Abhiyan 2021, the state government has decided to regularise colonies having 20-feet road width. However, occupancy in these colonies should be 60%. The relaxation is provided to invite more people to camps for procuring lease deeds.

news.title: About 90 houses built on Assam government tea estate land razed
news.para: Sources said Patharkandi circle authorities backed by Assam police and paramilitary forces evicted the families from the government land by using 20 excavators amid protests by settlers.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA's lists complaints against 3,600 developers
news.para: The MahaRERA website lists complaints against 3,600 projects from six revenue divisions in the state. These include projects where the hearing is complete or yet to be scheduled.

news.title: NTR district stocks up on seven lakh cubic metres of sand
news.para: Shortage of sand is a major concern for builders during monsoon season. Around 132 trucks and an earthmover were washed away in the floods at Chevitikallu sand reach in August 2021.

news.title: Haryana: NGT slaps Rs 115 crore fine on builders in Kundli
news.para: Notably, the complaint had also exposed the nexus between HSIIDC, HSPCB , HSVP and the local district administration who used to protect the said builders.

news.title: Municipal Corporation of Delhi's uniform property tax policy comes into effect
news.para: After the reunification of the three erstwhile corporations, the MCD announced that a uniform property tax slab would apply to areas under its jurisdiction. Earlier the three corporations had different slabs.
